  "finding": "The recognition-gated moat is MODEL-DEPENDENT: it needs a clean activation-level projection gap. gemma-2-2b has one (moat cuts ASR 0.50->0.25 at 0 benign over-refusal). Qwen2.5-1.5B's projections overlap (gating is ineffective and over-refuses). On SmolLM2-1.7B the projections overlap AND the underlying hardening is COUNTERPRODUCTIVE (unconditional ASR 0.58->0.92) \u2014 the extracted direction pushes the wrong way. Conclusion: you MUST characterize per-model (clean gap + direction validity) before deploying; naive hardening can backfire.",
